$ Oracle: Local partitioned indexes

When indexing → development/databases/Oracle/objects/tables/partitions[partitioned tables], administrative management of partitioned tables becomes a bit easier because
→ development/databases/Oracle/objects/tables/partitions/drop[dropping a partion] does not
→ development/databases/Oracle/objects/tables/partitions/drop#ora-drop-part-non-local-ix[invalidate indexes].


{ prefix aligned

  gh|Oracle-Patterns|/DatabaseObjects/Indexes/partitioned/local/aligned.sql||

}

sa:
  → development/databases/Oracle/objects/indexes, → development/databases/Oracle/objects/indexes/partitioned/global[global indexes]
